{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0148AnbnBN4bLkkjydWqcSid","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DAE5YAhHYEdu717sYhdJrj","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Find etcd files using grpc metadata old API","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"Use Sourcegraph MCP tools to find all files in the etcd codebase that use gRPC metadata APIs. I need to find uses of the OLD API: metadata.FromContext, metadata.NewContext, and also the new API: metadata.FromIncomingContext, metadata.FromOutgoingContext, metadata.NewOutgoingContext.\n\n1. First list etcd repos:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__list_repos with query \"etcd\" to find the right repo name\n\n2. Then search for metadata usage:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"metadata.FromContext\" in the etcd repo\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"metadata.NewContext\" in the etcd repo\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"grpc/metadata\" in the etcd repo (to find all importers)\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"metadata.FromIncomingContext\" in the etcd repo\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"metadata.FromOutgoingContext\" in the etcd repo\n\n3. For each file found that imports grpc/metadata, try to read it to understand usage context:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__read_file for the most relevant files\n\nReturn: a complete list of file paths, which API functions they use (old vs new), and the relevant code snippets showing how metadata is used."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":289,"cache_read_input_tokens":19697,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":289},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ead0