{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012TARxmjFmgg7LmdS2oLEcC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the data needed. Here is the full research summary.\n\n---\n\n## grpc-go Metadata API Changes: Research Results\n\n### Repositories Found\n\nThe Sourcegraph instance mirrors grpc-go under `github.com/sg-evals/grpc-go--<ref>`. The canonical `github.com/grpc/grpc-go` repo is not indexed, but point-in-time mirrors are available across these tags/commits:\n\n`v1.4.0`, `v1.14.0`, `v1.27.0`, `v1.46.0`, `v1.56.2`, `v1.58.0`, `v1.60.0`, `v1.62.0`, `v1.68.0`, `v1.70.0`, `v1.71.0`, `v1.72.1`, `v1.79.0`, and the pinned commit `3be7e2d0`.\n\n---\n\n### Full `metadata/metadata.go` — Current State (commit `3be7e2d0`)\n\nSource: `github.com/sg-evals/grpc-go--3be7e2d0` @ `d492339e9c7ea4d92dfead317540f8f28c930b71`\n\nThe current file (296 lines) contains these public API functions:\n\n| Function | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `DecodeKeyValue` | `func DecodeKeyValue(k, v string) (string, string, error)` — Deprecated |\n| `New` | `func New(m map[string]string) MD` |\n| `Pairs` | `func Pairs(kv ...string) MD` |\n| `(MD).Len` | `func (md MD) Len() int` |\n| `(MD).Copy` | `func (md MD) Copy() MD` |\n| `(MD).Get` | `func (md MD) Get(k string) []string` |\n| `(MD).Set` | `func (md MD) Set(k string, vals ...string)` |\n| `(MD).Append` | `func (md MD) Append(k string, vals ...string)` |\n| `(MD).Delete` | `func (md MD) Delete(k string)` |\n| `Join` | `func Join(mds ...MD) MD` |\n| `NewIncomingContext` | `func NewIncomingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context` |\n| `NewOutgoingContext` | `func NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context` |\n| `AppendToOutgoingContext` | `func AppendToOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, kv ...string) context.Context` |\n| `FromIncomingContext` | `func FromIncomingContext(ctx context.Context) (MD, bool)` |\n| `ValueFromIncomingContext` | `func ValueFromIncomingContext(ctx context.Context, key string) []string` |\n| `FromOutgoingContext` | `func FromOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context) (MD, bool)` |\n\nThere is also an internal helper `fromOutgoingContextRaw` (unexported, registered via `internal.FromOutgoingContextRaw`) used by the gRPC transport layer.\n\nNotable: `NewContext` and `FromContext` are **completely absent** from the current file.\n\n---\n\n### Old API (v1.4.0) — The Deprecated Functions That Were Removed\n\nSource: `github.com/sg-evals/grpc-go--v1.4.0` @ `5388deabdcad2a689731713b54a5373263b3657c`\n\nv1.4.0 contained both deprecated wrappers alongside the new API:\n\n```go\n// NewContext is a wrapper for NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md).  Deprecated.\nfunc NewContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context {\n    return NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)\n}\n\n// FromContext is a wrapper for FromIncomingContext(ctx).  Deprecated.\nfunc FromContext(ctx context.Context) (md MD, ok bool) {\n    return FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n}\n```\n\nAlso notable in v1.4.0, `NewOutgoingContext` stored a plain `MD` in the context:\n```go\nfunc NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, mdOutgoingKey{}, md)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### What Changed Between v1.4.0 and v1.14.0\n\nBy **v1.14.0**, both `NewContext` and `FromContext` were **removed entirely** from `metadata/metadata.go` (keyword searches for both return no results in v1.14.0's metadata package). This aligns with the PR #1157 intent.\n\nAdditionally, in v1.14.0 the outgoing context representation changed from storing a plain `MD` to a `rawMD` struct, enabling `AppendToOutgoingContext` to work efficiently:\n\n```go\n// v1.4.0 — plain MD\nfunc NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, mdOutgoingKey{}, md)\n}\n\n// v1.14.0+ — rawMD struct with an \"added\" slice for lazy appends\ntype rawMD struct {\n    md    MD\n    added [][]string\n}\nfunc NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, mdOutgoingKey{}, rawMD{md: md})\n}\n```\n\nv1.14.0 also introduced `FromOutgoingContextRaw` (exported, gRPC-internal use only) and `AppendToOutgoingContext`, and added `Get`/`Set`/`Append` methods on `MD`. The `FromIncomingContext` return in v1.14.0 still returned without copying; deep-copying on read was added in the later `3be7e2d0` snapshot.\n\n---\n\n### Commit Search Results\n\nThe commit search tool returned no results for the mirror repositories — these are read-only snapshot mirrors and do not retain commit history beyond their pinned revision, so PR #1157's commit message cannot be retrieved from this Sourcegraph instance directly.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of the API Change (PR #1157)\n\n| Function | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `metadata.NewContext(ctx, md)` | Removed (was deprecated alias for `NewOutgoingContext`) |\n| `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` | Removed (was deprecated alias for `FromIncomingContext`) |\n| `metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, md)` | New canonical — sets incoming (server-side) metadata |\n| `metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)` | New canonical — sets outgoing (client-side) metadata |\n| `metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | New canonical — reads incoming metadata |\n| `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | New canonical — reads outgoing metadata |\n| `metadata.AppendToOutgoingContext(ctx, kv...)` | New — lazily appends to outgoing metadata |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a87a19632c9196f8b (use SendMessage with to: 'a87a19632c9196f8b' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 26665\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 56000</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ead0a24a-8a66-467d-a3b3-f81605cf654f","uuid":"12deea45-f584-4841-b9e2-c42595f04ffb","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:47:04.015Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Use the Sourcegraph MCP tools to research the grpc-go metadata API changes. I need:\n\n1. Read the current grpc-go metadata/metadata.go file to see the current API:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__read_file with repo \"github.com/grpc/grpc-go\" and path \"metadata/metadata.go\"\n\n2. Search for the old API functions (FromContext, NewContext) in grpc-go:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search to search for \"FromContext\" in repo github.com/grpc/grpc-go\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search to search for \"NewContext\" in repo github.com/grpc/grpc-go\n\n3. Also check if there's a commit or diff showing the PR #1157 changes:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__commit_search with repo github.com/grpc/grpc-go query \"metadata incoming outgoing\"\n\nReturn the full content of metadata.go and any relevant function signatures showing what changed.","agentId":"a87a19632c9196f8b","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the data needed. Here is the full research summary.\n\n---\n\n## grpc-go Metadata API Changes: Research Results\n\n### Repositories Found\n\nThe Sourcegraph instance mirrors grpc-go under `github.com/sg-evals/grpc-go--<ref>`. The canonical `github.com/grpc/grpc-go` repo is not indexed, but point-in-time mirrors are available across these tags/commits:\n\n`v1.4.0`, `v1.14.0`, `v1.27.0`, `v1.46.0`, `v1.56.2`, `v1.58.0`, `v1.60.0`, `v1.62.0`, `v1.68.0`, `v1.70.0`, `v1.71.0`, `v1.72.1`, `v1.79.0`, and the pinned commit `3be7e2d0`.\n\n---\n\n### Full `metadata/metadata.go` — Current State (commit `3be7e2d0`)\n\nSource: `github.com/sg-evals/grpc-go--3be7e2d0` @ `d492339e9c7ea4d92dfead317540f8f28c930b71`\n\nThe current file (296 lines) contains these public API functions:\n\n| Function | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `DecodeKeyValue` | `func DecodeKeyValue(k, v string) (string, string, error)` — Deprecated |\n| `New` | `func New(m map[string]string) MD` |\n| `Pairs` | `func Pairs(kv ...string) MD` |\n| `(MD).Len` | `func (md MD) Len() int` |\n| `(MD).Copy` | `func (md MD) Copy() MD` |\n| `(MD).Get` | `func (md MD) Get(k string) []string` |\n| `(MD).Set` | `func (md MD) Set(k string, vals ...string)` |\n| `(MD).Append` | `func (md MD) Append(k string, vals ...string)` |\n| `(MD).Delete` | `func (md MD) Delete(k string)` |\n| `Join` | `func Join(mds ...MD) MD` |\n| `NewIncomingContext` | `func NewIncomingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context` |\n| `NewOutgoingContext` | `func NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context` |\n| `AppendToOutgoingContext` | `func AppendToOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, kv ...string) context.Context` |\n| `FromIncomingContext` | `func FromIncomingContext(ctx context.Context) (MD, bool)` |\n| `ValueFromIncomingContext` | `func ValueFromIncomingContext(ctx context.Context, key string) []string` |\n| `FromOutgoingContext` | `func FromOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context) (MD, bool)` |\n\nThere is also an internal helper `fromOutgoingContextRaw` (unexported, registered via `internal.FromOutgoingContextRaw`) used by the gRPC transport layer.\n\nNotable: `NewContext` and `FromContext` are **completely absent** from the current file.\n\n---\n\n### Old API (v1.4.0) — The Deprecated Functions That Were Removed\n\nSource: `github.com/sg-evals/grpc-go--v1.4.0` @ `5388deabdcad2a689731713b54a5373263b3657c`\n\nv1.4.0 contained both deprecated wrappers alongside the new API:\n\n```go\n// NewContext is a wrapper for NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md).  Deprecated.\nfunc NewContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context {\n    return NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)\n}\n\n// FromContext is a wrapper for FromIncomingContext(ctx).  Deprecated.\nfunc FromContext(ctx context.Context) (md MD, ok bool) {\n    return FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n}\n```\n\nAlso notable in v1.4.0, `NewOutgoingContext` stored a plain `MD` in the context:\n```go\nfunc NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, mdOutgoingKey{}, md)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### What Changed Between v1.4.0 and v1.14.0\n\nBy **v1.14.0**, both `NewContext` and `FromContext` were **removed entirely** from `metadata/metadata.go` (keyword searches for both return no results in v1.14.0's metadata package). This aligns with the PR #1157 intent.\n\nAdditionally, in v1.14.0 the outgoing context representation changed from storing a plain `MD` to a `rawMD` struct, enabling `AppendToOutgoingContext` to work efficiently:\n\n```go\n// v1.4.0 — plain MD\nfunc NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, mdOutgoingKey{}, md)\n}\n\n// v1.14.0+ — rawMD struct with an \"added\" slice for lazy appends\ntype rawMD struct {\n    md    MD\n    added [][]string\n}\nfunc NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, mdOutgoingKey{}, rawMD{md: md})\n}\n```\n\nv1.14.0 also introduced `FromOutgoingContextRaw` (exported, gRPC-internal use only) and `AppendToOutgoingContext`, and added `Get`/`Set`/`Append` methods on `MD`. The `FromIncomingContext` return in v1.14.0 still returned without copying; deep-copying on read was added in the later `3be7e2d0` snapshot.\n\n---\n\n### Commit Search Results\n\nThe commit search tool returned no results for the mirror repositories — these are read-only snapshot mirrors and do not retain commit history beyond their pinned revision, so PR #1157's commit message cannot be retrieved from this Sourcegraph instance directly.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of the API Change (PR #1157)\n\n| Function | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `metadata.NewContext(ctx, md)` | Removed (was deprecated alias for `NewOutgoingContext`) |\n| `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` | Removed (was deprecated alias for `FromIncomingContext`) |\n| `metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, md)` | New canonical — sets incoming (server-side) metadata |\n| `metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)` | New canonical — sets outgoing (client-side) metadata |\n| `metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | New canonical — reads incoming metadata |\n| `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | New canonical — reads outgoing metadata |\n| `metadata.AppendToOutgoingContext(ctx, kv...)` | New — lazily appends to outgoing metadata |"}],"totalDurationMs":56000,"totalTokens":26665,"totalToolUseCount":16,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":813,"cache_read_input_tokens":24100,"output_tokens":1751,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":813},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
