{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DAE5YAhHYEdu717sYhdJrj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete picture. Here is the full report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete gRPC Metadata API Usage in etcd (github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd, v3.5.17)\n\n### Summary\n\n**Old deprecated API (`metadata.FromContext`, `metadata.NewContext`): ZERO uses found.** The etcd codebase has been fully migrated to the new API. All usage is with the current gRPC metadata API.\n\n---\n\n### Files and Their API Usage\n\n#### NEW API — `metadata.FromOutgoingContext`\n\n| File | Function / Context | Snippet |\n|---|---|---|\n| `client/v3/ctx.go` | `WithRequireLeader`, `withVersion` | Reads outgoing MD to append/set leader key and API version key before making a gRPC call |\n| `client/v3/watch.go` | `streamKeyFromCtx` | Serializes outgoing MD to a string key for stream deduplication |\n| `client/v3/lease.go` | `closeRequireLeader` | Inspects outgoing MD of each keepalive context to find `RequireLeader`-flagged channels to close |\n| `server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` | lease proxy stream setup | Checks if the proxied stream's context carries the `require-leader` key |\n| `server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | watch proxy stream setup | Same leader check on the watch proxy stream context |\n\n#### NEW API — `metadata.NewOutgoingContext`\n\n| File | Function / Context | Snippet |\n|---|---|---|\n| `client/v3/ctx.go` | `WithRequireLeader`, `withVersion` | Creates/replaces outgoing context with updated MD pairs |\n| `client/v3/ctx_test.go` | `TestMetadataWithRequireLeader` | Test setup: creates outgoing context with MD before calling `WithRequireLeader` |\n| `client/v3/watch_test.go` | `TestStreamKeyFromCtx` | Test: creates outgoing contexts with various MD to verify stream key formatting |\n| `tests/integration/v3_grpc_test.go` | `TestGRPCRequireLeader`, `TestGRPCStreamRequireLeader` | Integration tests: sets `require-leader` metadata on outgoing context for KV.Put and Watch |\n| `tests/integration/v3_lease_test.go` | `TestV3LeaseFailover`, `TestV3LeaseRequireLeader` | Integration tests: sets `require-leader` metadata for LeaseKeepAlive streams |\n| `tests/integration/clientv3/watch_test.go` | `TestWatchCancel`, `testWatchOverlapContextCancel` | Integration tests: creates unique per-watcher outgoing contexts with different metadata to force separate gRPC streams |\n\n#### NEW API — `metadata.FromIncomingContext`\n\n| File | Function / Context | Snippet |\n|---|---|---|\n| `server/auth/store.go` | `authStore.AuthInfoFromCtx` (line 1166) | Extracts token from incoming gRPC metadata for authentication |\n| `server/auth/store.go` | TLS CommonName auth path (line 1134) | Checks for `grpcgateway-accept` header to detect gateway proxy requests and ignore CN auth |\n| `server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` | `getAuthTokenFromClient` | Extracts the auth token from the incoming server context for proxy forwarding |\n| `pkg/grpc_testing/recorder.go` | `toRequestInfo` | Test helper: reads `:authority` header from incoming context to record request info |\n| `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | `newUnaryInterceptor` (line 56) | Reads client API version and require-leader key from incoming unary RPC metadata |\n| `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | `newStreamInterceptor` (line 222) | Same checks for streaming RPCs |\n\n#### NEW API — `metadata.NewIncomingContext`\n\n| File | Function / Context | Snippet |\n|---|---|---|\n| `server/auth/store.go` | `WithRoot` / lease token injection (line 1300) | Injects a root auth token into the context as *incoming* metadata when called from local etcdserver (not over network) — comment explicitly notes: `\"use mdIncomingKey{} since it's called from local etcdserver\"` |\n| `server/auth/store_test.go` | `TestAuthInfoFromCtx` (lines 852, 864, 870, 876) | Test helper: simulates incoming gRPC context by wrapping contexts with token metadata to test `AuthInfoFromCtx` |\n\n#### `metadata.MD` type usage only (no `From*`/`New*` calls, `grpc/metadata` imported for the type)\n\n| File | Notes |\n|---|---|\n| `server/proxy/grpcproxy/adapter/chan_stream.go` | Uses `metadata.MD` as the type for header/trailer channels in the in-process `chanServerStream`/`chanClientStream` bridge; no context extraction calls |\n| `client/v3/retry_interceptor.go` | Imports `metadata` but uses it only indirectly via `withVersion(ctx)` calls (which themselves use `NewOutgoingContext`); no direct metadata calls in this file |\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **No deprecated API usage.** `metadata.FromContext` and `metadata.NewContext` (the pre-gRPC-1.0 API) do not appear anywhere in the codebase.\n\n2. **Clear client/server split:** Client-side code (`client/v3/`) exclusively uses `FromOutgoingContext`/`NewOutgoingContext` to attach metadata to outgoing calls. Server-side code (`server/`) exclusively uses `FromIncomingContext` to read metadata from arriving RPCs.\n\n3. **`NewIncomingContext` is used in one special case:** `server/auth/store.go` uses it to inject an auth token when the call comes from the local etcdserver process (not over the network), deliberately mimicking the incoming-metadata path so `AuthInfoFromCtx` works uniformly regardless of call origin."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2b3bc9da12f9ade9 (use SendMessage with to: 'a2b3bc9da12f9ade9' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44700\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 79663</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ead0a24a-8a66-467d-a3b3-f81605cf654f","uuid":"b94087fc-db57-4863-9554-897a5c301f52","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:47:33.285Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Use Sourcegraph MCP tools to find all files in the etcd codebase that use gRPC metadata APIs. I need to find uses of the OLD API: metadata.FromContext, metadata.NewContext, and also the new API: metadata.FromIncomingContext, metadata.FromOutgoingContext, metadata.NewOutgoingContext.\n\n1. First list etcd repos:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__list_repos with query \"etcd\" to find the right repo name\n\n2. Then search for metadata usage:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"metadata.FromContext\" in the etcd repo\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"metadata.NewContext\" in the etcd repo\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"grpc/metadata\" in the etcd repo (to find all importers)\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"metadata.FromIncomingContext\" in the etcd repo\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__keyword_search with query \"metadata.FromOutgoingContext\" in the etcd repo\n\n3. For each file found that imports grpc/metadata, try to read it to understand usage context:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__read_file for the most relevant files\n\nReturn: a complete list of file paths, which API functions they use (old vs new), and the relevant code snippets showing how metadata is used.","agentId":"a2b3bc9da12f9ade9","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete picture. Here is the full report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete gRPC Metadata API Usage in etcd (github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd, v3.5.17)\n\n### Summary\n\n**Old deprecated API (`metadata.FromContext`, `metadata.NewContext`): ZERO uses found.** The etcd codebase has been fully migrated to the new API. All usage is with the current gRPC metadata API.\n\n---\n\n### Files and Their API Usage\n\n#### NEW API — `metadata.FromOutgoingContext`\n\n| File | Function / Context | Snippet |\n|---|---|---|\n| `client/v3/ctx.go` | `WithRequireLeader`, `withVersion` | Reads outgoing MD to append/set leader key and API version key before making a gRPC call |\n| `client/v3/watch.go` | `streamKeyFromCtx` | Serializes outgoing MD to a string key for stream deduplication |\n| `client/v3/lease.go` | `closeRequireLeader` | Inspects outgoing MD of each keepalive context to find `RequireLeader`-flagged channels to close |\n| `server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` | lease proxy stream setup | Checks if the proxied stream's context carries the `require-leader` key |\n| `server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | watch proxy stream setup | Same leader check on the watch proxy stream context |\n\n#### NEW API — `metadata.NewOutgoingContext`\n\n| File | Function / Context | Snippet |\n|---|---|---|\n| `client/v3/ctx.go` | `WithRequireLeader`, `withVersion` | Creates/replaces outgoing context with updated MD pairs |\n| `client/v3/ctx_test.go` | `TestMetadataWithRequireLeader` | Test setup: creates outgoing context with MD before calling `WithRequireLeader` |\n| `client/v3/watch_test.go` | `TestStreamKeyFromCtx` | Test: creates outgoing contexts with various MD to verify stream key formatting |\n| `tests/integration/v3_grpc_test.go` | `TestGRPCRequireLeader`, `TestGRPCStreamRequireLeader` | Integration tests: sets `require-leader` metadata on outgoing context for KV.Put and Watch |\n| `tests/integration/v3_lease_test.go` | `TestV3LeaseFailover`, `TestV3LeaseRequireLeader` | Integration tests: sets `require-leader` metadata for LeaseKeepAlive streams |\n| `tests/integration/clientv3/watch_test.go` | `TestWatchCancel`, `testWatchOverlapContextCancel` | Integration tests: creates unique per-watcher outgoing contexts with different metadata to force separate gRPC streams |\n\n#### NEW API — `metadata.FromIncomingContext`\n\n| File | Function / Context | Snippet |\n|---|---|---|\n| `server/auth/store.go` | `authStore.AuthInfoFromCtx` (line 1166) | Extracts token from incoming gRPC metadata for authentication |\n| `server/auth/store.go` | TLS CommonName auth path (line 1134) | Checks for `grpcgateway-accept` header to detect gateway proxy requests and ignore CN auth |\n| `server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` | `getAuthTokenFromClient` | Extracts the auth token from the incoming server context for proxy forwarding |\n| `pkg/grpc_testing/recorder.go` | `toRequestInfo` | Test helper: reads `:authority` header from incoming context to record request info |\n| `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | `newUnaryInterceptor` (line 56) | Reads client API version and require-leader key from incoming unary RPC metadata |\n| `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | `newStreamInterceptor` (line 222) | Same checks for streaming RPCs |\n\n#### NEW API — `metadata.NewIncomingContext`\n\n| File | Function / Context | Snippet |\n|---|---|---|\n| `server/auth/store.go` | `WithRoot` / lease token injection (line 1300) | Injects a root auth token into the context as *incoming* metadata when called from local etcdserver (not over network) — comment explicitly notes: `\"use mdIncomingKey{} since it's called from local etcdserver\"` |\n| `server/auth/store_test.go` | `TestAuthInfoFromCtx` (lines 852, 864, 870, 876) | Test helper: simulates incoming gRPC context by wrapping contexts with token metadata to test `AuthInfoFromCtx` |\n\n#### `metadata.MD` type usage only (no `From*`/`New*` calls, `grpc/metadata` imported for the type)\n\n| File | Notes |\n|---|---|\n| `server/proxy/grpcproxy/adapter/chan_stream.go` | Uses `metadata.MD` as the type for header/trailer channels in the in-process `chanServerStream`/`chanClientStream` bridge; no context extraction calls |\n| `client/v3/retry_interceptor.go` | Imports `metadata` but uses it only indirectly via `withVersion(ctx)` calls (which themselves use `NewOutgoingContext`); no direct metadata calls in this file |\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **No deprecated API usage.** `metadata.FromContext` and `metadata.NewContext` (the pre-gRPC-1.0 API) do not appear anywhere in the codebase.\n\n2. **Clear client/server split:** Client-side code (`client/v3/`) exclusively uses `FromOutgoingContext`/`NewOutgoingContext` to attach metadata to outgoing calls. Server-side code (`server/`) exclusively uses `FromIncomingContext` to read metadata from arriving RPCs.\n\n3. **`NewIncomingContext` is used in one special case:** `server/auth/store.go` uses it to inject an auth token when the call comes from the local etcdserver process (not over the network), deliberately mimicking the incoming-metadata path so `AuthInfoFromCtx` works uniformly regardless of call origin."}],"totalDurationMs":79663,"totalTokens":44700,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1574,"cache_read_input_tokens":41610,"output_tokens":1515,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1574},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JdT1777gfLVSxaKxeD9rp9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me also look for the transitive metadata forwarding patterns in the proxy files. Let me check the specific proxy files mentioned to understand if there's metadata forwarding happening.\n\nFrom the research:\n1. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` - extracts auth token from incoming context for proxy forwarding\n2. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` - proxy stream setup\n3. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` - proxy stream setup\n\nThese proxy files are the \"critical\" metadata forwarding cases - they take incoming RPC metadata and forward it to outgoing RPCs. Let me check one of those files to understand the forwarding pattern.\n\n\nThe research agents have already given me what I need. Looking at the breaking changes: `metadata.FromContext` and `metadata.NewContext` have been removed and replaced with `metadata.FromIncomingContext`, `metadata.FromOutgoingContext`, and `metadata.NewOutgoingContext` respectively. The etcd codebase has been fully migrated with no old API usage remaining, and the proxy files in `server/proxy/grpcproxy/` handle the transitive metadata forwarding from incoming to outgoing RPCs.\n\nSince etcd has already completed the migration to the new API, the actual breakage risk is minimal—any code still using the old functions would simply fail to compile.\n\nThe key semantic issue is that `FromContext` was an alias for `FromIncomingContext`, so if someone mistakenly used it to read outgoing metadata, they'd silently lose that metadata at runtime rather than getting a compile error.\n\nThe proxy's metadata forwarding in `server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` demonstrates the correct pattern: extracting the auth token from incoming context and then adding it to the outgoing call.\n\nNow I'll compile the findings into the report and JSON output.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4241,"cache_read_input_tokens":19986,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4241},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ead0a24a-8a66-467d-a3b3-f81605cf654f","uuid":"96543f71-6a65-4070-ae9f-6c93094a0859"}
