{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SVd8yKnpiJb7LmXX6sptaX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a complete breakdown of how metadata flows from incoming to outgoing RPCs across these files:\n\n---\n\n## Metadata Forwarding Patterns in etcd's gRPC Proxy\n\n### 1. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` — Core Token Forwarding Primitives\n\nThis file is the heart of auth-token metadata forwarding. It contains three cooperating mechanisms:\n\n**Extracting the token from an incoming server context:**\n```go\nfunc getAuthTokenFromClient(ctx context.Context) string {\n    md, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n    if ok {\n        ts, ok := md[rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC]\n        if ok {\n            return ts[0]\n        }\n    }\n    return \"\"\n}\n```\n\n**Copying the token from one context into another (used in stream fanout):**\n```go\nfunc withClientAuthToken(ctx, ctxWithToken context.Context) context.Context {\n    token := getAuthTokenFromClient(ctxWithToken)\n    if token != \"\" {\n        ctx = context.WithValue(ctx, rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC, token)\n    }\n    return ctx\n}\n```\n\n**Unary client interceptor — reads token from incoming server context, injects it as `PerRPCCredentials` on the outgoing client call:**\n```go\nfunc AuthUnaryClientInterceptor(ctx context.Context, method string, req, reply interface{}, cc *grpc.ClientConn, invoker grpc.UnaryInvoker, opts ...grpc.CallOption) error {\n    token := getAuthTokenFromClient(ctx)\n    if token != \"\" {\n        tokenCred := &proxyTokenCredential{token}\n        opts = append(opts, grpc.PerRPCCredentials(tokenCred))\n    }\n    return invoker(ctx, method, req, reply, cc, opts...)\n}\n```\n\n**Stream client interceptor — reads token from `context.Value` (placed there by `withClientAuthToken`), injects it as `PerRPCCredentials`:**\n```go\nfunc AuthStreamClientInterceptor(ctx context.Context, desc *grpc.StreamDesc, cc *grpc.ClientConn, method string, streamer grpc.Streamer, opts ...grpc.CallOption) (grpc.ClientStream, error) {\n    tokenif := ctx.Value(rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC)\n    if tokenif != nil {\n        tokenCred := &proxyTokenCredential{tokenif.(string)}\n        opts = append(opts, grpc.PerRPCCredentials(tokenCred))\n    }\n    return streamer(ctx, desc, cc, method, opts...)\n}\n```\n\nThe `proxyTokenCredential` struct implements `credentials.PerRPCCredentials`, returning the token in `GetRequestMetadata` so it's attached as gRPC metadata on every outgoing call.\n\n**Pattern summary for unary:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext` → token string → `grpc.PerRPCCredentials` on outgoing call.  \n**Pattern summary for streams:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext` → `context.WithValue` → `ctx.Value` → `grpc.PerRPCCredentials` on outgoing stream.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` (lines 1–100) — Watch Stream Context Setup\n\nThe Watch proxy receives a server stream and derives a child context from it, which will carry the token downstream:\n\n```go\nfunc (wp *watchProxy) Watch(stream pb.Watch_WatchServer) (err error) {\n    // ...\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(stream.Context())\n    wps := &watchProxyStream{\n        ranges:   wp.ranges,\n        watchers: make(map[int64]*watcher),\n        stream:   stream,\n        // ctx carries the auth token from stream.Context()\n```\n\nThe `stream.Context()` already has the incoming gRPC metadata (including the auth token), and this is propagated to `watchProxyStream`. The `AuthStreamClientInterceptor` (registered on the client connection) then picks up the token via `context.Value` when outgoing watch streams are established.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` (lines 1–100) — Lease Proxy Context Propagation\n\nThe lease proxy passes the incoming `ctx` directly through to the upstream client calls, relying on the interceptor chain to forward the token:\n\n```go\nfunc (lp *leaseProxy) LeaseGrant(ctx context.Context, cr *pb.LeaseGrantRequest) (*pb.LeaseGrantResponse, error) {\n    rp, err := lp.leaseClient.LeaseGrant(ctx, cr, grpc.WaitForReady(true))\n    // ctx flows directly — AuthUnaryClientInterceptor handles token injection\n}\n\nfunc (lp *leaseProxy) LeaseRevoke(ctx context.Context, rr *pb.LeaseRevokeRequest) (*pb.LeaseRevokeResponse, error) {\n    r, err := lp.lessor.Revoke(ctx, clientv3.LeaseID(rr.ID))\n    // same pattern\n}\n```\n\nNo explicit token manipulation here — the `ctx` passed in is the server-side context with incoming metadata, and `AuthUnaryClientInterceptor` installed on the `clientv3.Client` reads the token and injects it into the outgoing request.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` — Server-Side Metadata Inspection\n\nThe server interceptors read incoming metadata but do **not** forward it; they inspect it for routing decisions:\n\n**Unary interceptor** reads `MetadataClientAPIVersionKey` for metrics and `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` for leader checks:\n```go\nmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\nif ok {\n    ver, vs := \"unknown\", md.Get(rpctypes.MetadataClientAPIVersionKey)\n    // ...\n    if ks := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]; len(ks) > 0 && ks[0] == rpctypes.MetadataHasLeader {\n        if s.Leader() == types.ID(raft.None) {\n            return nil, rpctypes.ErrGRPCNoLeader\n        }\n    }\n}\nreturn handler(ctx, req)\n```\n\n**Stream interceptor** does the same and additionally wraps the stream in a `serverStreamWithCtx` for leader-loss cancellation:\n```go\nmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ss.Context())\nif ok {\n    // ...MetadataRequireLeaderKey check...\n    ctx := newCancellableContext(ss.Context())\n    ss = serverStreamWithCtx{ctx: ctx, ServerStream: ss}\n}\nreturn handler(srv, ss)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `server/auth/store.go` (lines 1130–1310) — Auth Token Extraction and Synthetic Injection\n\n**`AuthInfoFromCtx`** (lines 1162–1188) extracts the token from the incoming metadata for authentication:\n```go\nfunc (as *authStore) AuthInfoFromCtx(ctx context.Context) (*AuthInfo, error) {\n    md, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n    // ...\n    ts, ok := md[rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC]\n    if !ok {\n        ts, ok = md[rpctypes.TokenFieldNameSwagger]\n    }\n    token := ts[0]\n    authInfo, uok := as.authInfoFromToken(ctx, token)\n    // ...\n    return authInfo, nil\n}\n```\n\n**`WithRoot`** (lines 1263–1301) synthetically injects a root token into the **incoming** context for internal server-initiated calls (e.g., lease revocation):\n```go\nfunc (as *authStore) WithRoot(ctx context.Context) context.Context {\n    // generate a root token...\n    mdMap := map[string]string{\n        rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC: token,\n    }\n    tokenMD := metadata.New(mdMap)\n    // NOTE: uses NewIncomingContext — treats this as if the token arrived from a client\n    return metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, tokenMD)\n}\n```\n\nThe TLS client-certificate path (lines 1130–1160) also uses `metadata.FromIncomingContext` to detect the `grpcgateway-accept` header and suppress CN-based auth for gateway requests.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Full Flow\n\n```\nClient RPC (with token in gRPC metadata)\n    │\n    ▼\ngrpcproxy handler (Watch/Lease/KV)\n    │  metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx) → token string\n    │  withClientAuthToken: stored in context.Value\n    │\n    ▼\nAuthUnaryClientInterceptor / AuthStreamClientInterceptor\n    │  reads token via getAuthTokenFromClient / ctx.Value\n    │  wraps in proxyTokenCredential\n    │  appends grpc.PerRPCCredentials(tokenCred) to call options\n    │\n    ▼\nUpstream etcd server RPC (token re-attached as gRPC metadata)\n    │\n    ▼\nserver interceptor.go\n    │  metadata.FromIncomingContext → MetadataClientAPIVersionKey, MetadataRequireLeaderKey\n    │\n    ▼\nauth/store.go AuthInfoFromCtx\n    │  metadata.FromIncomingContext → TokenFieldNameGRPC / TokenFieldNameSwagger\n    └─ authenticates the request\n```\n\nThe key design decision: the proxy does **not** use `metadata.NewOutgoingContext` to copy the whole metadata map. Instead, it extracts only the auth token, stores it in the context or as a `PerRPCCredentials` call option, and lets the gRPC client interceptor layer re-attach it as fresh outgoing metadata. Internal server calls use `metadata.NewIncomingContext` (via `WithRoot`) to simulate an incoming-metadata context, keeping the token lookup path uniform."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0dcece868a8ffc74 (use SendMessage with to: 'a0dcece868a8ffc74' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 26363\ntool_uses: 7\nduration_ms: 56063</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ead0a24a-8a66-467d-a3b3-f81605cf654f","uuid":"75e7fdb3-c269-487e-b6f7-781c550f6195","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:48:48.263Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Use Sourcegraph MCP tools to read specific etcd proxy files to understand metadata forwarding patterns. I need to understand how metadata flows from incoming to outgoing RPCs.\n\n1. First find the right etcd repo name:\n   - Use mcp__sourcegraph__list_repos with query \"etcd\"\n   - The repo is likely \"github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd\" or similar\n\n2. Read these specific files:\n   - mcp__sourcegraph__read_file for \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go\" \n   - mcp__sourcegraph__read_file for \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\" (first 100 lines)\n   - mcp__sourcegraph__read_file for \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go\" (first 100 lines)\n   - mcp__sourcegraph__read_file for \"server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go\" (focus on lines around metadata usage)\n   - mcp__sourcegraph__read_file for \"server/auth/store.go\" (focus on lines 1130-1170 and 1295-1310)\n\nReturn the full relevant code snippets showing how metadata flows from incoming to outgoing contexts in these proxy/interceptor files.","agentId":"a0dcece868a8ffc74","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a complete breakdown of how metadata flows from incoming to outgoing RPCs across these files:\n\n---\n\n## Metadata Forwarding Patterns in etcd's gRPC Proxy\n\n### 1. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` — Core Token Forwarding Primitives\n\nThis file is the heart of auth-token metadata forwarding. It contains three cooperating mechanisms:\n\n**Extracting the token from an incoming server context:**\n```go\nfunc getAuthTokenFromClient(ctx context.Context) string {\n    md, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n    if ok {\n        ts, ok := md[rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC]\n        if ok {\n            return ts[0]\n        }\n    }\n    return \"\"\n}\n```\n\n**Copying the token from one context into another (used in stream fanout):**\n```go\nfunc withClientAuthToken(ctx, ctxWithToken context.Context) context.Context {\n    token := getAuthTokenFromClient(ctxWithToken)\n    if token != \"\" {\n        ctx = context.WithValue(ctx, rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC, token)\n    }\n    return ctx\n}\n```\n\n**Unary client interceptor — reads token from incoming server context, injects it as `PerRPCCredentials` on the outgoing client call:**\n```go\nfunc AuthUnaryClientInterceptor(ctx context.Context, method string, req, reply interface{}, cc *grpc.ClientConn, invoker grpc.UnaryInvoker, opts ...grpc.CallOption) error {\n    token := getAuthTokenFromClient(ctx)\n    if token != \"\" {\n        tokenCred := &proxyTokenCredential{token}\n        opts = append(opts, grpc.PerRPCCredentials(tokenCred))\n    }\n    return invoker(ctx, method, req, reply, cc, opts...)\n}\n```\n\n**Stream client interceptor — reads token from `context.Value` (placed there by `withClientAuthToken`), injects it as `PerRPCCredentials`:**\n```go\nfunc AuthStreamClientInterceptor(ctx context.Context, desc *grpc.StreamDesc, cc *grpc.ClientConn, method string, streamer grpc.Streamer, opts ...grpc.CallOption) (grpc.ClientStream, error) {\n    tokenif := ctx.Value(rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC)\n    if tokenif != nil {\n        tokenCred := &proxyTokenCredential{tokenif.(string)}\n        opts = append(opts, grpc.PerRPCCredentials(tokenCred))\n    }\n    return streamer(ctx, desc, cc, method, opts...)\n}\n```\n\nThe `proxyTokenCredential` struct implements `credentials.PerRPCCredentials`, returning the token in `GetRequestMetadata` so it's attached as gRPC metadata on every outgoing call.\n\n**Pattern summary for unary:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext` → token string → `grpc.PerRPCCredentials` on outgoing call.  \n**Pattern summary for streams:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext` → `context.WithValue` → `ctx.Value` → `grpc.PerRPCCredentials` on outgoing stream.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` (lines 1–100) — Watch Stream Context Setup\n\nThe Watch proxy receives a server stream and derives a child context from it, which will carry the token downstream:\n\n```go\nfunc (wp *watchProxy) Watch(stream pb.Watch_WatchServer) (err error) {\n    // ...\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(stream.Context())\n    wps := &watchProxyStream{\n        ranges:   wp.ranges,\n        watchers: make(map[int64]*watcher),\n        stream:   stream,\n        // ctx carries the auth token from stream.Context()\n```\n\nThe `stream.Context()` already has the incoming gRPC metadata (including the auth token), and this is propagated to `watchProxyStream`. The `AuthStreamClientInterceptor` (registered on the client connection) then picks up the token via `context.Value` when outgoing watch streams are established.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` (lines 1–100) — Lease Proxy Context Propagation\n\nThe lease proxy passes the incoming `ctx` directly through to the upstream client calls, relying on the interceptor chain to forward the token:\n\n```go\nfunc (lp *leaseProxy) LeaseGrant(ctx context.Context, cr *pb.LeaseGrantRequest) (*pb.LeaseGrantResponse, error) {\n    rp, err := lp.leaseClient.LeaseGrant(ctx, cr, grpc.WaitForReady(true))\n    // ctx flows directly — AuthUnaryClientInterceptor handles token injection\n}\n\nfunc (lp *leaseProxy) LeaseRevoke(ctx context.Context, rr *pb.LeaseRevokeRequest) (*pb.LeaseRevokeResponse, error) {\n    r, err := lp.lessor.Revoke(ctx, clientv3.LeaseID(rr.ID))\n    // same pattern\n}\n```\n\nNo explicit token manipulation here — the `ctx` passed in is the server-side context with incoming metadata, and `AuthUnaryClientInterceptor` installed on the `clientv3.Client` reads the token and injects it into the outgoing request.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` — Server-Side Metadata Inspection\n\nThe server interceptors read incoming metadata but do **not** forward it; they inspect it for routing decisions:\n\n**Unary interceptor** reads `MetadataClientAPIVersionKey` for metrics and `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` for leader checks:\n```go\nmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\nif ok {\n    ver, vs := \"unknown\", md.Get(rpctypes.MetadataClientAPIVersionKey)\n    // ...\n    if ks := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]; len(ks) > 0 && ks[0] == rpctypes.MetadataHasLeader {\n        if s.Leader() == types.ID(raft.None) {\n            return nil, rpctypes.ErrGRPCNoLeader\n        }\n    }\n}\nreturn handler(ctx, req)\n```\n\n**Stream interceptor** does the same and additionally wraps the stream in a `serverStreamWithCtx` for leader-loss cancellation:\n```go\nmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ss.Context())\nif ok {\n    // ...MetadataRequireLeaderKey check...\n    ctx := newCancellableContext(ss.Context())\n    ss = serverStreamWithCtx{ctx: ctx, ServerStream: ss}\n}\nreturn handler(srv, ss)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `server/auth/store.go` (lines 1130–1310) — Auth Token Extraction and Synthetic Injection\n\n**`AuthInfoFromCtx`** (lines 1162–1188) extracts the token from the incoming metadata for authentication:\n```go\nfunc (as *authStore) AuthInfoFromCtx(ctx context.Context) (*AuthInfo, error) {\n    md, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n    // ...\n    ts, ok := md[rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC]\n    if !ok {\n        ts, ok = md[rpctypes.TokenFieldNameSwagger]\n    }\n    token := ts[0]\n    authInfo, uok := as.authInfoFromToken(ctx, token)\n    // ...\n    return authInfo, nil\n}\n```\n\n**`WithRoot`** (lines 1263–1301) synthetically injects a root token into the **incoming** context for internal server-initiated calls (e.g., lease revocation):\n```go\nfunc (as *authStore) WithRoot(ctx context.Context) context.Context {\n    // generate a root token...\n    mdMap := map[string]string{\n        rpctypes.TokenFieldNameGRPC: token,\n    }\n    tokenMD := metadata.New(mdMap)\n    // NOTE: uses NewIncomingContext — treats this as if the token arrived from a client\n    return metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, tokenMD)\n}\n```\n\nThe TLS client-certificate path (lines 1130–1160) also uses `metadata.FromIncomingContext` to detect the `grpcgateway-accept` header and suppress CN-based auth for gateway requests.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Full Flow\n\n```\nClient RPC (with token in gRPC metadata)\n    │\n    ▼\ngrpcproxy handler (Watch/Lease/KV)\n    │  metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx) → token string\n    │  withClientAuthToken: stored in context.Value\n    │\n    ▼\nAuthUnaryClientInterceptor / AuthStreamClientInterceptor\n    │  reads token via getAuthTokenFromClient / ctx.Value\n    │  wraps in proxyTokenCredential\n    │  appends grpc.PerRPCCredentials(tokenCred) to call options\n    │\n    ▼\nUpstream etcd server RPC (token re-attached as gRPC metadata)\n    │\n    ▼\nserver interceptor.go\n    │  metadata.FromIncomingContext → MetadataClientAPIVersionKey, MetadataRequireLeaderKey\n    │\n    ▼\nauth/store.go AuthInfoFromCtx\n    │  metadata.FromIncomingContext → TokenFieldNameGRPC / TokenFieldNameSwagger\n    └─ authenticates the request\n```\n\nThe key design decision: the proxy does **not** use `metadata.NewOutgoingContext` to copy the whole metadata map. Instead, it extracts only the auth token, stores it in the context or as a `PerRPCCredentials` call option, and lets the gRPC client interceptor layer re-attach it as fresh outgoing metadata. Internal server calls use `metadata.NewIncomingContext` (via `WithRoot`) to simulate an incoming-metadata context, keeping the token lookup path uniform."}],"totalDurationMs":56063,"totalTokens":26363,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13243,"cache_read_input_tokens":10631,"output_tokens":2488,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13243},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015z7jTF6LLBkeQxfkXkY9JQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me write the impact report and the JSON output.\n\nHere's what I know:\n\n**Breaking API Changes in PR #1157:**\n- `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` → removed (was deprecated alias for `FromIncomingContext`)\n- `metadata.NewContext(ctx, md)` → removed (was deprecated alias for `NewOutgoingContext`)\n\n**Replacement API:**\n- `metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)` — reads metadata from incoming server RPCs\n- `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` — reads metadata from outgoing client RPCs\n\n\n- `metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, md)` — sets incoming metadata (server simulation)\n- `metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)` — sets outgoing metadata (client RPCs)\n- `metadata.AppendToOutgoingContext(ctx, kv...)` — appends to outgoing metadata\n\nThe etcd codebase is already fully migrated with no usage of the old APIs, and all files are using the new split API instead.\n\nLooking at the specific files, the client-side code uses the outgoing context functions for leader version metadata and stream key generation, while the server-side code uses incoming context functions for auth token extraction and forwarding through the proxy layer. The test files mirror these patterns with their own setup and verification logic. arding)\n9. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` — context propagation (no direct metadata calls, but passes through incoming context)\n10. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` — context propagation (indirect via interceptors)\n11. `server/proxy/grpcproxy/adapter/chan_stream.go` — metadata.MD type usage only\n12. `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` — FromIncomingContext (require-leader, API version)\n13. `pkg/grpc_testing/recorder.go` — FromIncomingContext (test helper)\n14. `tests/integration/v3_grpc_test.go` — NewOutgoingContext (integration tests)\n15. `tests/integration/v3_lease_test.go` — NewOutgoingContext (integration tests)\n16. `tests/integration/clientv3/watch_test.go` — NewOutgoingContext (integration tests)\n\nThe etcd codebase has already completed its migration, so there are no actual breakages to worry about. Before the migration happened, code using the old `metadata.FromContext` or `metadata.NewContext` functions would have failed to compile, and any code relying on `FromContext` to read outgoing metadata would have experienced runtime behavior changes. The proxy layer in `server/proxy/grpcproxy/` is particularly critical since it handles metadata forwarding, with `util.go` extracting incoming context metadata.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3656,"cache_read_input_tokens":24227,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3656},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ead0a24a-8a66-467d-a3b3-f81605cf654f","uuid":"bd973063-d3f9-4721-8d60-f6f25f0f995a"}
