e primary metadata forwarding site.\",\n      \"critical\": true,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": \"incoming_to_outgoing\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\",\n      \"api_used\": [],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"description\": \"Propagates stream.Context() (which carries incoming metadata) to child contexts. No direct metadata API calls; relies on AuthStreamClientInterceptor in util.go for token forwarding.\",\n      \"critical\": true,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": \"context_propagation\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go\",\n      \"api_used\": [],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"description\": \"Passes incoming ctx directly to upstream client calls. AuthUnaryClientInterceptor in util.go handles token extraction and re-injection.\",\n      \"critical\": true,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": \"context_propagation\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/adapter/chan_stream.go\",\n      \"api_used\": [\"metadata.MD type only\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"description\": \"Uses metadata.MD as a type for header/trailer channels in the in-process channel stream bridge. No FromContext or NewContext calls.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go\",\n      \"api_used\": [\"FromIncomingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"description\": \"Both unary and stream interceptors read MetadataClientAPIVersionKey (for metrics) and MetadataRequireLeaderKey (for leader gating) from incoming metadata. Read-only; no forwarding.\",\n      \"critical\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"pkg/grpc_testing/recorder.go\",\n      \"api_used\": [\"FromIncomingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"description\": \"Test helper reads :authority header from incoming context to record request info.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"tests/integration/v3_grpc_test.go\",\n      \"api_used\": [\"NewOutgoingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"description\": \"Integration tests set require-leader metadata on outgoing contexts for KV.Put and Watch RPCs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"tests/integration/v3_lease_test.go\",\n      \"api_used\": [\"NewOutgoingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"description\": \"Integration tests set require-leader metadata for LeaseKeepAlive streams.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"tests/integration/clientv3/watch_test.go\",\n      \"api_used\": [\"NewOutgoingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"description\": \"Integration tests create unique per-watcher outgoing contexts with distinct metadata to force separate gRPC streams.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"critical_metadata_forwarding\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go\",\n      \"pattern\": \"incoming-to-outgoing token forwarding via PerRPCCredentials\",\n      \"functions\": [\"getAuthTokenFromClient\", \"withClientAuthToken\", \"AuthUnaryClientInterceptor\", \"AuthStreamClientInterceptor\"],\n      \"flow\": \"metadata.FromIncomingContext(serverCtx) → token string → grpc.PerRPCCredentials → outgoing RPC metadata\",\n      \"risk_if_unmigrated\": \"Compile error (FromContext not found). Semantic risk: if old FromContext were used it would still correctly read incoming metadata since proxy IS the server side, but client/v3 code that used FromContext to read outgoing metadata would silently get (nil, false).\",\n      \"safety_note\": \"Uses PerRPCCredentials rather than metadata.NewOutgoingContext for forwarding, which sidesteps the incoming/outgoing slot confusion entirely.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"server/auth/store.go\",\n      \"function\": \"WithRoot\",\n      \"pattern\": \"synthetic incoming-context injection for internal server calls\",\n      \"flow\": \"metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, tokenMD) so AuthInfoFromCtx (which calls FromIncomingContext) finds the root token\",\n      \"risk_if_unmigrated\": \"Silent auth failure at runtime — if NewOutgoingContext (old NewContext) were used, the token would be in the wrong slot and authentication would silently fail for all internal server-initiated operations.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\",\n      \"pattern\": \"context propagation — stream.Context() carries incoming metadata downstream\",\n      \"risk_if_unmigrated\": \"None directly; relies on util.go interceptors for token forwarding.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"server/proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go\",\n      \"pattern\": \"context passthrough — incoming ctx passed directly to upstream client calls\",\n      \"risk_if_unmigrated\": \"None directly; relies on util.go interceptors for token forwarding.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"migration_status\": \"complete\",\n  \"old_api_usage_count\": 0,\n  \"summary\": \"The etcd codebase has been fully migrated to the split incoming/outgoing metadata API introduced in grpc-go PR #1157. No uses of the removed metadata.FromContext or metadata.NewContext exist. 13 files would have had compile errors on the old API; 1 file (server/auth/store.go WithRoot) would additionally have had a silent runtime auth failure. The most architecturally critical file is server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go, which implements auth token forwarding from incoming server RPCs to outgoing proxied RPCs using a PerRPCCredentials pattern that is robust to the incoming/outgoing slot distinction.\",\n  \"severity\": {\n    \"level\": \"low\",\n    \"rationale\": \"Migration is already complete. No compile errors or runtime regressions will occur when upgrading grpc-go past the PR #1157 removal point. Historical severity of the API change was high — the removed functions introduced silent metadata loss bugs for any code that used FromContext to read outgoing contexts or NewContext/NewOutgoingContext followed by FromIncomingContext in the same context chain.\"\n  },\n  \"ownership\": \"grpc proxy and auth subsystems (server/proxy/grpcproxy/, server/auth/, server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/, client/v3/)\"\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
