{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":292706,"duration_api_ms":347180,"num_turns":11,"result":"Both files have been written. Here's a summary of findings:\n\n## Key Findings\n\n### Breaking API Changes (PR #1157)\n`metadata.FromContext` and `metadata.NewContext` were **completely removed**. They were deprecated aliases:\n- `FromContext` → `FromIncomingContext` (server-side reads)\n- `NewContext` → `NewOutgoingContext` (client-side writes)\n\nThe new split API adds `FromOutgoingContext`, `NewIncomingContext`, and `AppendToOutgoingContext`.\n\n### etcd Migration Status: **Complete — zero old API usage**\n\n16 files import `google.golang.org/grpc/metadata`. None use the removed functions. All have been migrated to the correct split API.\n\n### Critical: Metadata Forwarding\n\n**`server/proxy/grpcproxy/util.go`** is the core forwarding site:\n- `getAuthTokenFromClient` → `metadata.FromIncomingContext` → token string\n- `AuthUnaryClientInterceptor` / `AuthStreamClientInterceptor` re-attach via `grpc.PerRPCCredentials`\n\nThis uses a **PerRPCCredentials pattern** (not `metadata.NewOutgoingContext`) which sidesteps the incoming/outgoing slot confusion entirely — it's robust by design.\n\n**`server/auth/store.go` `WithRoot`** is the subtler risk: it uses `NewIncomingContext` to inject a root token for internal server calls. If it had used `NewOutgoingContext` (the old `NewContext`), `AuthInfoFromCtx` would silently fail to find the token — a **runtime auth failure with no compile error**.\n\n### Severity: Low\netcd is fully migrated and safe to upgrade grpc-go past this change.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ead0a24a-8a66-467d-a3b3-f81605cf654f","total_cost_usd":0.8293283999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":12,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20233,"cache_read_input_tokens":216908,"output_tokens":9240,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":202